snippet.title: The Shining
snippet.description: Academy Award winner Jack Nicholson and Shelley Duvall star in director Stanley Kubrick's disturbing adaptation of Stephen King's blockbuster horror novel. When writer Jack Torrance (Nicholson)--who has a history of alcoholism and child abuse--takes a job as winter caretaker for a hotel high in the Rocky Mountains, he, his wife (Duvall) and their psychic young son will be isolated until spring. But once the first blizzard closes the road out, the accumulated power of evil deeds committed at the hotel begins to drive Jack mad. Now there may be no escape for his wife and son in this haunting madness, memory and family violence.

snippet.title: Virtual Behind the Scenes at Romano Gymnasium
snippet.description:
Join former UMD Bulldog Basketball Head Coaches and current athletic administrators, Karen Stromme and Gary Holquist in a Virtual Bulldogs Behind the Scenes tour of Romano Gymnasium exploring recent renovations including historical perspectives.

Romano Gymnasium has been the home of Bulldog Men’s and Women’s Basketball and Volleyball for over a half-century. The historic facility opened December 12, 1953 and underwent a renovation in 1986 as well as a significant remodel throughout 2019-2020. Romano Gymnasium is the largest indoor gathering space on the UMD campus and one of the larger venues in Northern Minnesota. The space is a highly visible area of campus that is seen by all students, University employees, and community. It is often looked at as the “front porch” of the institution. Romano Gymnasium is much more than an athletic team space, event space, and teaching space - it is a community space.

*This event was recorded via Zoom on October, 20 2020.*

Bulldogs Behind the Scenes is a UMD alumni event that gives you an inside look at local industry leaders. Alumni and friends will enjoy facility tours, access to company leadership, and connecting with each other through curiosity and learning.

Learn more about our virtual programs at d.umn.edu/alumni

You can learn more about Romano by visiting https://umdbulldogs.com/sports/2013/8/30/RomanoGym.aspx

snippet.title: Virtual Behind the Scenes at Romano Gymnasium
snippet.description:
Join former UMD Bulldog Basketball Head Coaches and current athletic administrators, Karen Stromme and Gary Holquist in a Virtual Bulldogs Behind the Scenes tour of Romano Gymnasium exploring recent renovations including historical perspectives.

Romano Gymnasium has been the home of Bulldog Men’s and Women’s Basketball and Volleyball for over a half-century. The historic facility opened December 12, 1953 and underwent a renovation in 1986 as well as a significant remodel throughout 2019-2020. Romano Gymnasium is the largest indoor gathering space on the UMD campus and one of the larger venues in Northern Minnesota. The space is a highly visible area of campus that is seen by all students, University employees, and community. It is often looked at as the “front porch” of the institution. Romano Gymnasium is much more than an athletic team space, event space, and teaching space - it is a community space.

*This event was recorded via Zoom on October, 20 2020.*

Bulldogs Behind the Scenes is a UMD alumni event that gives you an inside look at local industry leaders. Alumni and friends will enjoy facility tours, access to company leadership, and connecting with each other through curiosity and learning.

Learn more about our virtual programs at d.umn.edu/alumni

You can learn more about Romano by visiting https://umdbulldogs.com/sports/2013/8/30/RomanoGym.aspx

Hi guys! We've got the brand new Thomas & Friends™ Talking Thomas & Percy Train Set today on Kids Toys Play! Sodor is usually an island in the middle of the ocean, but sometimes, with the Fisher-Price® Thomas & Friends™ Talking Thomas & Percy Train Set, Sodor can also be in the living room. This highly detailed playset features favorite places from the island of Sodor, including the Vicarstown Bridge, the Railyard, the Brendam docks, and Blue Mountain. It also includes motorized Thomas and Percy train engines who recognize and talk to each other when they meet on the track! Young conductors can help Thomas and Percy work together by dropping boulders down in the Blue Mountain cave for them to load and unload along with other cargo at Bulstrode the boat and by creating their own exciting adventures all around Sodor.

Motorized Thomas and Percy engines stop to talk with each other when they meet on the track, and both have cargo cars for loading and unloading around the island
Kid-controlled track switches and a control panel allow little engineers to stop engines for side-by-side interactions and control which way they go
Combine this track with any other Thomas & Friends™ train set to create even bigger Sodor adventures! (Track sets sold separately and subject to availability.)
